{:name=>"Borsao Bole 2014", :varietal=>"Grenache", :vintage=>2014, :producer=>"Borsao", :wine_type=>"Red Wine", :region=>"", :country=>"Spain", :price=>nil, :description=>"", :image_url=>"www.wine.com/labels/260804h.jpg", :expert_rating=>90.0, :professional_reviews=>"Bole is an old brand that is being refurbished. The 2014 Bole is a blend of Garnacha with 30% Syrah aged in second- and third-year French oak barrels for five months and kept in tank until bottling. This was first produced in 2007 (together with Berola) and it's relaunched now. It has a meaty nose, with aromas reminiscent of Syrah that give it a Rhône profile. It has a spicy touch, but almost unnoticeable oak, with perhaps a touch of creaminess. The palate is intense with some roasted flavors, very tasty, with fine-grained tannins and a supple finish. 144,000 bottles.", :user_rating=>0.0, :upc=>"08412423120999", :user_rating_count=>0, :store_one=>nil, :link_one=>nil, :store_two=>nil, :link_two=>nil, :store_three=>nil, :link_three=>nil}, 

