{:name=>"Chateau de Vaudieu Val de Dieu Chateauneuf-du-Pape 2011", :varietal=>"Rhone Red Blends", :vintage=>2011, :producer=>"Chateau de Vaudieu", :wine_type=>"Red Wine", :region=>"Chateauneuf-du-Pape, Rhone", :country=>"France", :price=>86, :description=>"", :image_url=>"www.wine.com/labels/165610h.jpg", :expert_rating=>93.0, :professional_reviews=>"More refined and elegant, as well as textured, the 2011 Chateauneuf du Pape Val de Dieu (66% Grenache, 27% Mourvedre and the balance Syrah, aged in a combination of barrique and demi-muid) dishes out gorgeous notes of cassis, blackberry, creamy licorice and candied flowers on the nose. Medium to full-bodied and pure, supple and textured on the palate, it is a sexy, hedonistic beauty that’s hard to resist. It too should have over a decade of longevity. Drink now-2021.", :user_rating=>0.0, :upc=>"", :user_rating_count=>0, :store_one=>"Link to Buy", :link_one=>"http://www.google.com/aclk?sa=l&ai=DChcSEwjg39bSwa3XAhUSHhsKHQ0HCZ0YABAFGgJ3bA&sig=AOD64_2M8jupvSgho4zkfJSkSMchr0-ckA&ctype=5&ved=0ahUKEwiO9tDSwa3XAhUI5oMKHRfhCAIQ2CkIGTAA&adurl=", :store_two=>nil, :link_two=>nil, :store_three=>nil, :link_three=>nil}, 

